HEADWORD: Weather-board
<hw>Weath"er-board`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>To
nail boards upon so as to lap one over another, in order to exclude
rain, snow, etc.</def> <rj><au>Gwilt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
